cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper investigates the effects of social feedback on user behavior in online communities, which involves social interactions and user-generated content. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also analyzes the impact of negative feedback on the quality of future posts, which relates to the study of online reputation and trust, and could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The paper also examines the perception of content quality by the community, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses network analysis to study the polarization of the community, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and the analysis of online content and user behavior.
